			<title>EGA 2011: Vote now and win a Wii U!</title>
			<link>http://www.european-games-award.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=191:ega-2011-voting-started</link>
			<guid>http://www.european-games-award.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=191:ega-2011-voting-started</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.european-games-award.com/index.php?option=com_wrapper&amp;view=wrapper&amp;Itemid=8"><img style="margin-bottom: 5px; border-width: 0px; border-style: none;" alt="win_wiiu" src="http://www.european-games-award.com/images/stories/win_wiiu.gif" height="241" width="631" /></a></p>
<p> </p>
<p>The EGA 2011 has startet and everyone is invited to vote for his favorite game in over 20 categories. In the past year over 400 games were released in europe and we selected more than 100 of the best games for you to be europes finest. For the first time you will be able to not just vote for retail and online games but for Add-Ons and DLCs also! Take your vote and be part of the greatest public vote in gaming history: European Game Awards 2011.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Every registered voter, automatically takes part in our lottery. The prize will beNintendo's next generation Console the Wii U!</p>
