		<item>
			<title>What is the European Games Award?</title>
			<link>http://www.european-games-award.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=110:what-is-the-european-games-award</link>
			<guid>http://www.european-games-award.com/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=110:what-is-the-european-games-award</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p>The European Games Award is the first award exclusively for European  video and computer game developers, which lets professionals and gamers  from all over Europe participate in the voting for the best games.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>The award ceremony – after having been held in Cologne (Germany) for  two years – will then take place in a different European capital each  year. The première of the European Games Award on August 14th 2010 took place in an extraordinary location: on the Pure Liner, an event ship, which left Niehler Harbor in Cologne and sailed along the Rhine  during the award ceremony.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>The European Games Award demonstrates how many important  games are developed in Europe, and honors the work of  the developers, publishers and all those involved in the production and  marketing of games.</p>]]></description>
